# Work Division: 2 Developers, Zero Dependencies

Split by **user-facing side** so there are zero shared files.

---

## 👤 Person A — Candidate-Side Features

> Everything under `app/candidate/`, `app/api/profile/`, and `app/api/applications/`

### Task A1: GitHub Sync API + Profile Button
**Goal:** Candidate clicks "Sync GitHub" → skills auto-populate from repos

#### [NEW] `app/api/profile/github-sync/route.ts`
- `POST` handler: reads `githubUsername` from the candidate's profile
- Calls `fetchGitHubProfile()` from `lib/github.ts`
- Merges `derivedSkills` into `hardSkills` (keep manual entries, add/update GitHub ones)
- Updates `githubStats` and `lastGithubSync` on the CandidateProfile
- Auth check: must be CANDIDATE role

#### [NEW] `app/api/profile/embedding/route.ts`
- `POST` handler: generates an OpenAI embedding for the candidate's profile
- Calls `buildCandidateProfileText()` → `generateEmbedding()` → `upsertCandidateEmbedding()`
- Triggered after profile save or GitHub sync
- Auth check: must be CANDIDATE role

#### [MODIFY] `app/candidate/profile/page.tsx`
- Add "Sync GitHub" button (visible when `githubUsername` is filled)
- Show sync status / last sync timestamp
- Add "Generate AI Profile" button (calls embedding endpoint)
- Show GitHub stats section (repos, stars, languages) when data exists

---

### Task A2: Candidate Applications Page
**Goal:** Candidate can see all jobs they applied to + application status

#### [NEW] `app/api/applications/route.ts`
- `GET` handler: returns all applications for the logged-in candidate
- Includes job title, company name, status (PENDING/SHORTLISTED/REJECTED/HIRED), applied date
- Auth check: must be CANDIDATE role

#### [NEW] `app/candidate/applications/page.tsx`
- Table/card list of all applied jobs with status badges
- Filter by status (All / Pending / Shortlisted / Rejected)
- Link to job detail page
- Empty state: "No applications yet → Browse Jobs"

---

### Task A3: Skill Gap Analysis Page
**Goal:** Candidate selects a job → sees which skills they're missing and what to improve

#### [NEW] `app/api/gap-analysis/route.ts`
- `GET ?jobId=xxx` handler: compares candidate's skills against job requirements
- Returns per-skill: `{ skill, candidateLevel, requiredLevel, gap, suggestion }`
- Auth check: must be CANDIDATE role

#### [NEW] `app/candidate/gap-analysis/page.tsx`
- Job selector dropdown (from published jobs)
- Uses existing `SkillGapChart` component from `components/charts/SkillChart.tsx`
- Shows skill-by-skill breakdown with actionable suggestions
- "Your match score for this job: X%"

