## 🔒 Zero-Overlap Guarantee

```
Person A files          Person B files
─────────────────       ─────────────────
app/api/profile/*       app/api/search/*
app/api/applications/*  app/api/admin/*
app/api/gap-analysis/*  app/recruiter/search/*
app/candidate/*         components/matching/*
                        app/admin/*
                        middleware.ts
                        prisma/seed.ts
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Neither person modifies any shared lib file.** Both import from `lib/` and `services/` as read-only. Zero merge conflicts guaranteed.

---

## ✅ Shared Files (READ-ONLY for both)

These files are **already complete** and neither person should modify them:

- `lib/matching.ts` — scoring engine
- `lib/github.ts` — GitHub scraper
- `lib/supabase.ts` — pgvector operations
- `lib/auth.ts` — NextAuth config
- `lib/prisma.ts` — DB client
- `services/openai.ts` — embedding generator
- `components/ui/*` — all UI primitives
- `prisma/schema.prisma` — database schema

---

## Verification Plan

### Person A — Testing
1. **GitHub Sync:** Register as candidate → set GitHub username → click "Sync GitHub" → verify `hardSkills` updated in profile
2. **Applications Page:** Apply to 2-3 jobs → navigate to `/candidate/applications` → verify all applications shown with correct statuses
3. **Skill Gap:** Select a job on gap analysis page → verify chart renders with skill comparisons

### Person B — Testing
1. **Semantic Search:** As recruiter → type "Cloud infrastructure expert" → toggle to Semantic mode → verify different results than keyword mode
2. **XAI Tooltips:** View matches for a job → expand MatchCard → verify human-readable explanations appear
3. **Admin Dashboard:** Login as admin → navigate to `/admin` → verify stats render
4. **Seed Data:** Run `npm run db:seed` → verify demo data created without errors

> [!TIP]
> Both people can work on separate git branches and merge at the end — since files don't overlap, merges will be automatic.
